(208, 0, '_transient_feed_867bd5c64f85878d03a060509cd2f92c', 'a:4:{s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:3:"rss";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:3:"\n\n\n";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:7:"version";s:3:"2.0";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:7:"channel";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:61:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"WordPress Planet";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:28:"http://planet.wordpress.org/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"language";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"en";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:47:"WordPress Planet - http://planet.wordpress.org/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"item";a:50:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Plugin Releases for 4/17";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=9904";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/QdCZLqi6R4k/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1339:"<h3>New plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/imageshare/"><strong>ImageShare</strong></a> adds social bookmarking buttons to images in your blog posts.</p>\n<p><a href="http://erikras.com/wordpress-plugins/javascript-flickr-badge/"><strong>Javascript Flickr Badge</strong></a> uses pure javascript to place a Flickr badge in your widget-enabled sidebar to display recent photos.</p>\n<p><a href="http://t31os.wordpress.com/2011/04/15/my-first-plugin-on-wordpress-extend/"><strong>Post UI Tabs</strong></a> allows you to create jQuery tabs inside your posts, pages or post types using simple shortcodes inside the post editor.</p>\n<h3>Updated plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/ie6-upgrade-option/"><strong>IE6 Upgrade Option</strong></a> displays a warning message, simply and politely informing the user that their browser is out of date while providing links to download newer, more optimal browser choices.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.designchemical.com/blog/index.php/wordpress-plugins/wordpress-plugin-jquery-vertical-mega-menu-widget/"><strong>jQuery Vertical Mega Menu</strong></a> allows you to quickly and easily create vertical mega menus from any WordPress custom menu.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/QdCZLqi6R4k" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sun, 17 Apr 2011 13:00:07 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"James Huff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Dev Blog: Summer WordCamps 2011";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:33:"http://wordpress.org/news/?p=1785";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"http://wordpress.org/news/2011/04/summer-wordcamps-201/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6014:"<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p>Looking for something fun to do during your summer vacation? Why not check out a WordCamp! WordCamps are locally-organized casual conferences of, by, and for WordPress users, developers, and enthusiasts just like you. The focus of a WordCamp is to foster face-to-face connections and collaboration among the local WordPress crowd, but there are usually some out-of-towners there as well. Here are the WordCamps that have been approved so far for the summer:</p>\n<p>April 16: <a href="http://wordcampseattle.org/">WordCamp Seattle</a> in Seattle, WA. This weekend! After taking a year off, WordCamp Seattle is back with tracks for bloggers, designers, and developers. This year they&#8217;ll feature a lineup including presentations by both local speakers and visitors like core committer Andrew Nacin, as well as an Ignite session of lightning talks at the end of the day.</p>\n<p>May 5: <a href="http://wordcampdevelopers.com/">WordCamp Vancouver (Developer Edition)</a> in Vancouver, BC. This one-day WordCamp is aimed purely at developers working on the WordPress platform, and will not have content aimed at bloggers (as previous Vancouver WordCamps have). I predict we will start seeing more of these types of niche WordCamps moving forward, because they will mean smaller, more intimate events that allow more collaboration (and make it easier to find venues!). Note that we&#8217;re working with the organizers to get the tickets to a more reasonable price, so keep your eyes open this week if you&#8217;ve held off on buying a ticket because of the price tag.</p>\n<p>May 7: <a href="http://wordcamp-switzerland.ch/">WordCamp Switzerland</a> in Brugg, Switzerland. This one will cover a wide range of topics, including getting started with WordPress, advanced development topics, BuddyPress, and an inside look at running a WordPress-based business.</p>\n<p>May 14: <a href="http://www.ocwordcamp.com/">WordCamp Orange County</a> in Orange, CA. Already sold out! Orange County had their first WordCamp last year, and the organizers have put together another great event this time around.</p>\n<p>May 14: <a href="http://paris14mai2011.wordcamp.fr/">WordCamp Paris</a> in Paris, France. One of the last true unconference-style WordCamps, the Paris group will plan their schedule the morning of the event like they do at BarCamps. WordCamp Paris had one of the best WordCamp t-shirts ever a couple of years ago. And it&#8217;s in Paris in the spring.</p>\n<p>May 21–22: <a href="http://wordcampraleigh.com/">WordCamp Raleigh</a> in Raleigh, NC. Repeat organizers from the Raleigh WordPress Meetup Group are just starting to select speakers and put together their plans, but if it is anything like last year, the venue will be packed with WordPress professionals (and maybe there will be cookies). I&#8217;ll be attending this one, as will Nacin.</p>\n<p>June 4–5: <a href="http://2011.reno.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp Reno-Lake Tahoe</a> in Reno, NV. Organized by a WordPress core UI group contributor, WordCamp Reno-Lake Tahoe is taking place in Reno and has a packed schedule full of visiting experts.</p>\n<p>June 11–12: <a href="http://www.wckansascity.org/">WordCamp Kansas City</a> in Overland Park, KS. With publisher, designer, and developer tracks, Kansas City&#8217;s WordCamp will have a little something for everyone, presented in large part by local speakers.</p>\n<p>June 17–19: <a href="http://wordcampcolumbus.com/">WordCamp Columbus</a> in Columbus, OH. WordCamp Columbus has a new organizer this year and is bringing the focus more firmly onto WordPress (and less on social media). Their 3-day event includes an entire day for newbies, and another for non-profits, a nice addition to the usual blogger/developer tracks.</p>\n<p>July 9–10: <a href="http://wcmtl.org/">WordCamp Montreal</a> in Montreal, Quebec. This group consistently puts on a great every year. If you register now, you can still get a $10 discount and get both days for only $30 (with sessions in both English and French to reflect the bilingual nature of the city). Montreal plays host to a number of <a href="http://www.montreal.com/tourism/festivals/index.html">festivals</a> throughout the year, and this weekend is no different, including festivals for the arts, comedy, tango, and even circus arts.</p>\n<p>July 16: <a href="http://2011.sandiego.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp San Diego</a> in San Diego, CA. First WordCamp in San Diego! They have talking about this for over a year, and are now starting to really ramp up the planning. They&#8217;re finalizing their venue right now, and I would expect a great roster of speakers.</p>\n<p>July 16-17: <a href="http://wiki.wordcampuk.org/Main_Page">WordCamp Portsmouth</a> in Portsmouth, UK. The annual WordCamp UK that moves from city to city each year alights this year in Portsmouth. This one is notable because Mike Little, co-founder of WordPress, is part of the organizing team.</p>\n<p>July 23–24: <a href="http://wordcampboston.com/">WordCamp Boston</a> in Boston, MA. Another one just about to lock down some details and get starting with speaker selection, etc. An easy train ride from so many places, and not in the middle of winter this year!</p>\n<p><a href="http://2011.chicago.wordcamp.org">WordCamp Chicago</a> has new organizers this year and is looking for a venue before deciding on a date, but hopes to happen this summer (hopefully late July). If you would be interested in donating a venue to this popular event, please <a href="http://2011.chicago.wordcamp.org/">contact them</a>. <a href="http://www.wordcampportland.org/">WordCamp Portland</a> is looking for a venue for September, also.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ll hold off on posting fall events until later in the summer since there a lot in the planning stages now. To get the most up-to-date information, visit <a href="http://central.wordcamp.org/schedule/">WordCamp Central</a>.</p>\n<p>Hope to see you at a WordCamp soon!</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sat, 16 Apr 2011 23:06:55 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Jane Wells";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:81:"WPCandy: WordCamp Seattle will be live streamed today, starting 9am Pacific/UTC-8";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=17100";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:116:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/iCY7rOXpIqQ/wordcamp-seattle-2011-will-be-live-streamed-today-starting-9am";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2111:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17100"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17101" title="WordCamp Seattle Live Stream (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/wordcampseattlelivestream-teaser.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="250" /></a></p><p>WordCamp Seattle, this weekend&#8217;s WordPress event <em><a title="WPCandy coverage of WordCamp Seattle 2011" href="http://wpcandy.com/at/wordcamp-seattle">de jour</a></em>, will be live streamed on their blog starting at 9:00am Pacific (UTC-8). Of the three tracks taking place today, the User/Blogger track and the Development track will each be live streamed.</p><ul><li><span><a title="WordCamp Seattle live stream for the User/Blogger track" href="http://live.blazestreaming.com/wcsea/2011/blogger.html">Watch the User/Blogger stream</a></span></li><li><span><a title="Watch the WordCamp Seattle live stream for the Development track" href="http://live.blazestreaming.com/wcsea/2011/developer.html">Watch the Development stream</a></span></li><li><span><a title="WPCandy WordCamp Seattle liveblog" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblogged/wordcamp-seattle-2011">Watch the WPCandy liveblog</a></span></li></ul><p>See what I did there? We&#8217;ll also be augmenting the WordCamp Seattle live streams with our own <a title="WPCandy WordCamp Seattle liveblog" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblogged/wordcamp-seattle-2011">liveblogging</a>. We&#8217;ll be in every session, so it should be fun finding out just how nuts the liveblog will become.</p><p>I&#8217;m also curious: as you look at <a title="WordCamp Seattle agenda" href="http://wordcampseattle.org/agenda/">today&#8217;s schedule</a>, which presentations look most interesting to you? If you were here, which sessions would you be sure not to miss? Who would you want to meet?</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17100">WordCamp Seattle will be live streamed today, starting 9am Pacific/UTC-8</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sat, 16 Apr 2011 14:36:49 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:50:"Weblog Tools Collection: Send us Plugins to Review";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=9901";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/FOop3WUZA7Q/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1092:"<p>A week ago, <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2011/04/08/plugin-reviews-inspections-and-audits/">we asked</a> if you&#8217;d be interested in seeing a few plugin reviews from us. I&#8217;m happy to say that the response was overwhelmingly positive. As of today, 96.97% said &#8220;Of course I would!&#8221; and only 3.03% said &#8220;Yawn, boring!&#8221;</p>\n<p>With that said, <a href="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/submit-plugins-for-review/">the new plugin review submission form</a> is ready to go!</p>\n<p>Is there a plugin that you’d like reviewed? Maybe you aren’t sure if it’s the right plugin for you, or maybe you want to know how it stacks up against the competition? Well, please let us know, and we just might review it!</p>\n<p>Please note that this is a service for the readers of Weblog Tools Collection. Developer-submitted review requests will be discarded.</p>\n<p>Well, what are you waiting for? Let&#8217;s get some reviews lined up!</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/FOop3WUZA7Q" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sat, 16 Apr 2011 13:00:05 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"James Huff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:93:"WPCandy: Pro Theme Design launches true testing bed for themes, new blog devoted to Elemental";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=17079";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:107:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/oQmFIaCvysM/pro-theme-design-launches-true-testing-bed-for-themes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2084:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17079"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17080" title="Pro Theme Design testing themes (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/prothemedesignthemetesting-teaser.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="272" /></a></p><p>This piece of news falls under the &#8220;cool news we didn&#8217;t quite get to right when it happened&#8221; category. Ben Gillbanks of Pro Theme Design (which <a title="Theme Madness Round 1 winners" href="http://wpcandy.com/announces/theme-madness-2011-round-1-day-2-and-3-winners">survived Round 1</a> of Theme Madness and will play again <a title="Pro Theme Design in Theme Madness" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">next week</a>) launched a new <a title="Pro Theme Design testing ground" href="http://prothemedesign.com/preview/">testing ground</a> for their paid WordPress themes.</p><p>Instead of a demo filled with example content, potential customers can now create a site using WordPress Multisite and apply a theme they would like to test out. Then, the theme can be used in just about every which way (aside from modifying its files, of course) to give the user a solid idea of what to expect when they purchase and install it.</p><p>What about all of the extra demonstration sites cluttering up Pro Theme Design&#8217;s world wide home? They thought of that: all created sites are cleared out every 36 hours. What do you think of this method, and have you seen any other theme developers or services using it?</p><p>While you&#8217;re digging into noteworthy Pro Theme Design activity, have a look at their blog for <em>Elemental</em> theme users and developers called <a title="Elemental Hub for users of Elemental" href="http://elementalhub.com/">Elemental Hub</a>.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17079">Pro Theme Design launches true testing bed for themes, new blog devoted to Elemental </a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 23:12:00 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"WPCandy: The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/I9Ugf-7rTxg/wordcamp-seattle-2011";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59668:"<a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17062" title="WPCandy WordCamp Seattle Liveblog (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/wordcampseattleliveblog-teaser.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="224" /></a>WPCandy will be at WordCamp Seattle this weekend (see <a title="WPCandy covers WordCamp Seattle" href="http://wpcandy.com/at/wordcamp-seattle">all of our coverage</a>), and of course it wouldn’t be a proper WordCamp without a WPCandy liveblog. This is the post to bookmark and watch: we’ll be updating this liveblog from now until we head back on Sunday. The real interesting stuff will come during the speaker’s sessions tomorrow, of course, which is when we’ll really be updating this liveblog the most.Liveblog starts just after the jump! (Just a heads up: due to changing the time zone to be correct right after the first session, the order of entries is off for a couple of hours. <em>Just to keep things interesting.</em>)<span id="more-17060"></span><hr /> <div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-17060"><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17190"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:57 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Wrapped up, applause for Scott.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17189"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:56 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Question now about the security breach, or &#8220;the incident&#8221;. They&#8217;ve had an overhaul security since then, audited everything. Not too much they can say about it, of course, due to security.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17187"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:55 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;Before we build a new feature, we think about how we can track the benefits. Then we can measure whether it was a good use of time.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17183"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Brian Krogsgard at 11:55 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>When they talk about new features for WordPress.com, they pay a lot of attention to stats. They want to understand how new features are being used. &#8220;How often is something clicked?&#8221; &#8220;Once it&#8217;s clicked, will they come back to use it again?&#8221; etc. etc. They want to know the tradeoff between the developers time and the benefit of the feature to users.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17186"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:54 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;If you had a like button now, I know that you wouldn&#8217;t click on it.&#8221;</p><p><em>Self deprecating win.</em></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17185"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:52 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Question is about how Automattic brought in its first VIP clients. Scott recommends asking Matt about it, but it sounds like was personal connections, people Matt knew and reached out to.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17184"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:51 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;Will Twitter destory blogging?&#8221;</p><p>&#8220;A lot of tweets are links to blog posts.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17182"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:50 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Talking various competitors to WordPress now. There&#8217;s actually a decent discussion over <a title="Is Tumblr the new WordPress? And great discussion on WordPress competitors" href="http://wpcandy.com/thinks/is-tumblr-the-new-wordpress">on this editorial post</a> about the same topic.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17181"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Brian Krogsgard at 11:48 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>The next few versions of Jetpack will be all about new features. Scott gave email subscriptions as an example of one feature on the way.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17180"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:47 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;If WordPress didn&#8217;t exist you would all be very sad. Where would you guys be today? You&#8217;d be at BlankCamp.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17179"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:46 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;Our systems guy, <a title="Barry of Automattic" href="http://automattic.com/about/">Barry</a>, is amazing. He&#8217;s like&#8230; the future of our species.&#8221;</p><p>New standard for compliments has been set.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17177"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:44 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a href="https://twitter.com/drawmark/status/59295378595520512"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17178" title="Mark Kaufman''s tweet" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-16-at-9.44.16-AM.png" alt="" width="531" height="216" /></a></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17176"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:43 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;Are you a developer? You&#8217;re a designer? Oh, I don&#8217;t want to talk to you then.&#8221; <em>laughs</em></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17175"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:43 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Question from the crowd: &#8220;You want an intern?&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17173"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:41 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>There are approximately 50 or 60 P2 blogs within Automattic. Not all are very active, some are dormant.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17169"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Brian Krogsgard at 11:41 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;Be aggressive about trying out plugins, and conservative about what you keep and maintain&#8221; &#8211; Scott on a question asking how many plugins are too many.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17171"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:40 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a href="https://twitter.com/trepmal/status/59294748233564161"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17172" title="Kailey''s tweet" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-16-at-9.39.52-AM.png" alt="" width="469" height="188" /></a></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17170"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:37 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Talking downsides of their system now. Seems to be: not everyone works best that way, certain social/emotional cues are hard to catch via text, etc.</p><p>&#8220;We tend to be almost too polite.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17168"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:35 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Recommends <a title="CodePoet.com" href="http://codepoet.com/">CodePoet.com</a> as a place to find reliable WordPress professionals.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17166"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:34 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;We depend a lot on the WordPress community to police itself.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17164"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:32 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a href="https://twitter.com/nacin/status/59292603849523200"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17165" title="Andrew Nacin''s tweet" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-16-at-9.31.21-AM.png" alt="" width="511" height="221" /></a></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17162"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:30 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Response to question: WordPress.com Publicize (social feature) can be added to Jetpack, but it isn&#8217;t being done yet. &#8220;Request noted.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17137"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Aaron Kugler at 11:29 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;There should be as little user-interface as possible. Imagine going to the bathroom and turning on the light. Only instead of flipping a switch, you have to go to the fuse box and start flipping switches then mess with the lighting, fading in and out. That would be annoying.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17161"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:29 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>It&#8217;s cool to see Scott in person talking. We&#8217;re always <a title="Scott Berkun on WPCandy" href="http://wpcandy.com/profiles/scott-berkun">mentioning him</a> on the blog.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17159"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:28 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a href="http://twitpic.com/4lmci5"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17160" title="WordCamp Seattle opening presentation crowd" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/278179277.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="358" /></a></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17156"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:26 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a rel="attachment wp-att-17158" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblog_entry/auto-draft-132/attachment/2011-04-16-09-24-13"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17158" title="Jetpack planning stages" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/2011-04-16-09.24.13-600x450.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" /></a></p><p><a rel="attachment wp-att-17157" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblog_entry/auto-draft-132/attachment/img_0534"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17157" title="Planning screens for Jetpack" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0534-600x448.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="448" /></a></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17154"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:24 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-17155" title="WordCamp Seattle 2011 Wi-fi connection" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-16-at-9.23.18-AM-300x188.png" alt="" width="300" height="188" /></p><p>Pretty impressive Wi-fi connection here. No complaints.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17153"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:22 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;You can see in this picture, that because we&#8217;re used to working distributed, so when we&#8217;re together it&#8217;s pretty awkward. We stare off into space, we don&#8217;t talk&#8230;&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17152"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:21 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Scott&#8217;s talking about <a title="Jetpack" href="http://jetpack.me/">Jetpack</a>, <a title="Jetpack discussed on WPCandy" href="http://wpcandy.com/?s=jetpack">heard of it</a>?</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17151"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:19 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;Apparently I&#8217;m not supposed to worship the sun yet.&#8221;</p><p>I&#8217;ll just let you refer to the recordings to make sense of that one.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17150"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:17 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Good analogies:</p><ul><li><span>IRC is like the hallway. There&#8217;s always a group of people in chat rooms.</span></li><li><span>Skype is for small team meetings.</span></li><li><span>P2 is a combination of status updates from Twitter with the retention ability of blogs. (Not really an analogy I guess.)</span></li></ul><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17149"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:16 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Automattic communicates entirely via IRC, Skype, and <a title="P2 WordPress theme" href="http://p2theme.com/">P2</a>. Talking about how Automattic doesn&#8217;t use email to communicate like most do.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17148"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:14 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;We recently released the 25,000th version of WordPress.com&#8230; We believe the only way we learn is deploying.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17146"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:13 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a rel="attachment wp-att-17147" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblog_entry/auto-draft-128/attachment/img_0533"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17147" title="List of Automattic principles" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0533-600x448.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="448" /></a></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17145"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:11 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;We don&#8217;t believe job titles are very important. We don&#8217;t believe where you work is important. We don&#8217;t even believe how long you work. We think it&#8217;s important what you get done.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17144"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:10 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a title="Automattic map of employees" href="http://automattic.com/map/">Automattic map of 70 or so odd employees</a>.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17143"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:10 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Regarding the distribution of Automattic employees: &#8220;We are everywhere. Like ninjas. We&#8217;re places you don&#8217;t expect us to be.&#8221;</p><p>Sounds like a threat, no?</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17142"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:09 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Scott&#8217;s background is as a writer, back before he moved to WordPress. He&#8217;s talking about how writing is important to the world, important to keep sacred.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17140"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:08 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a href="https://twitter.com/certifiedkory/status/59286007492771840"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17141" title="Kory McDow''s tweet" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-16-at-9.07.53-AM.png" alt="" width="533" height="182" /></a></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17139"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:07 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Happiness Engineering team is what Automattic/WordPress.com calls their support team. And every employee who is hired has to spend three weeks in support first, before doing anything else. Clever idea.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17138"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:06 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Turns out not a lot of folks here get many comments/day. New project: WPCandy will comment on all blogs. <em>Everywhere</em>.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17135"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:05 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a rel="attachment wp-att-17136" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblog_entry/auto-draft-121/attachment/img_0532"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17136" title="WordPress.com stats slide" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0532-600x448.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="448" /></a></p><p>Nearly 20,000,000 blogs on WordPress.com. Referencing <a title="WordPress.com Stats" href="http://en.wordpress.com/stats">this page</a>.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17117"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Aaron Kugler at 11:05 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;Currently there are almost twenty million blogs across WordPress.com&#8221;- Scott Berkun</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17134"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:04 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>I&#8217;m just kidding.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17133"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:03 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Scott Berkun just started breakdancing up there. Really odd.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17132"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:02 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>WordPress.com makes money three primary ways:</p><ol><li><span>Ads</span></li><li><span>Upgrades</span></li><li><span>VIP</span></li></ol><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17131"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 11:01 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>If you&#8217;re watching from home, remember the hashtag to follow is <a title="WordCamp Seattle hashtag" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wcsea">#wcsea</a>.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17130"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:59 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Explaining the difference between WordPress.com and WordPress.org. I&#8217;m glad, because I&#8217;ve been wondering about that one <em>for a while</em>.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17129"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:58 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Scott&#8217;s getting going now. Going to be some time for FAQ at the end. Any questions you would like asked? Leave them in the comments or hit us up <a title="WPCandy on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/wpcandy">on Twitter</a>.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17128"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:56 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Talking about the <a title="Seattle WordPress Meetup" href="http://www.meetup.com/SeattleWordPressMeetup/">Seattle WordPress Meetup</a>. It&#8217;s held at TechStars, if you&#8217;re local to Seattle. <em>Or</em>, if you love traveling hundreds of miles for local events.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17127"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:54 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;The bathrooms are kind of&#8230; meager offerings.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17125"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:53 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a href="https://twitter.com/arianna/status/59280357140344832"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17126" title="Arianna O''Dell''s tweet" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-16-at-8.52.27-AM.png" alt="" width="529" height="180" /></a></p><p>Aw, sad day.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17124"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:51 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;We&#8217;re using these cameras to record and live stream. So, please try not to stand in front of them.&#8221;</p><p>Thanking sponsors now. Microsoft up first.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17122"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:51 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a rel="attachment wp-att-17123" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblog_entry/auto-draft-112/attachment/img_0530"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17123" title="How is WordPress.com made?" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0530-e1302969059163-600x448.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="448" /></a></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17116"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:48 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Opening remarks happening now.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17222"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Justin Vela at 10:41 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Justin is describing their pricing structure as a way to figure out the market and what is out there.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17115"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:41 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>First up today is an all-track presentation by <a title="Scott Berkun''s profile on WordCamp Seattle blog" href="http://wordcampseattle.org/speaker/scott-berkun/">Scott Berkun</a>, Team Social lead at WordPress.com for Automattic. The presentation title is, appropriately, &#8220;How is WordPress.com Made?&#8221; Still a few minutes before things really get going here.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17219"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Justin Vela at 10:39 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>What is your percentage of overseas interest?</p><p>&#8220;About 1/3 so far.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17220"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:39 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Test</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17113"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:37 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a rel="attachment wp-att-17114" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblog_entry/17113/attachment/img_0529"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17114" title="View from our table at WordCamp Seattle 2011" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0529-e1302968069839-600x448.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="448" /></a></p><p>Our view from our table. Place is filling up! I guess that&#8217;s what <a title="WordCamp Seattle 2011 sells out" href="http://wpcandy.com/reports/350-attendees-at-wordcamp-seattle-2011">350 attendees</a> will do, eh?</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17213"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Justin Vela at 10:36 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Aren&#8217;t you looking in the rear view mirror with this?</p><p>&#8220;Well, yes. But we believe WordPress is a better platform for it.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17216"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Justin Vela at 10:34 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a rel="attachment wp-att-17217" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblog_entry/auto-draft-159/attachment/2011-04-16-10-31-07"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17217" title="Justin Sainton presenting at WordCamp Seattle 2011" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/2011-04-16-10.31.07-600x450.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" /></a></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17215"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:32 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Will&#8217;s now showing of his method for simplifying Ajax handlers. Refer to his slides for his class.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17111"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:32 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a rel="attachment wp-att-17112" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblog_entry/17111/attachment/img_0527"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17112" title="WPCandy shirts at the front table at WordCamp Seattle 2011" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0527-e1302967911857-600x448.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="448" /></a></p><p>Arrived and set up space for handing out WPCandy shirts at the front registration tables. Be sure to pick one up!</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17214"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:31 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>We&#8217;ll likely have the blogging track covered here as well by the next hour. Rest of the team is running a quick errand.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17212"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:30 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>When Justin Vela talks about Justin Sainton in the other room, I like to pretend he&#8217;s speaking in the third person, like royalty.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17208"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Justin Vela at 10:29 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Go to groupdealsplugin.com to check out what Justin is working on.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17109"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:29 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a href="https://twitter.com/toddflorence/status/59273996188913664"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17110" title="Todd Florence''s tweet" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/Screen-shot-2011-04-16-at-8.27.48-AM.png" alt="" width="540" height="264" /></a></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17211"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:26 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Not to go too inside baseball, but live blogging sessions with lots of code examples (which is a good thing) is tough. Great presentation, hard to quantify it here.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17209"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:24 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a rel="attachment wp-att-17210" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblog_entry/17209/attachment/img_0537"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17210" title="Audience in the dev track room for Will Anderson''s talk" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0537-e1302974638280-600x448.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="448" /></a></p><p>The current audience in the development track room.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17206"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:22 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>His slides include code examples, showing how to load up Javascript on only certain pages, or admin, or custom post type, etc.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17200"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Justin Vela at 10:21 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>&#8220;Custom post types are the coolest thing since&#8230;&#8230; well I guess pages.&#8221;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17188"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Brian Krogsgard at 10:21 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Good advice from Will: &#8220;You don&#8217;t have to run a custom script on every page.&#8221; You can pull it in where needed to save load times.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17204"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:20 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a rel="attachment wp-att-17205" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblog_entry/17204/attachment/img_0536"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17205" title="Will Anderson at WordCamp Seattle 2011" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0536-600x448.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="448" /></a></p><p>Talking <code>wp_enqueue_script()</code>, and generally how to start using Ajax in WordPress.</p><p>Did I mention I like that I was able to stay in the same place? Yup, no need to move yet.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17203"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:16 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Recommends using &#8220;jQuery&#8221; instead of the dollar symbol, for compatibility&#8217;s sake.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17202"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:14 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Quick overview of what Ajax is. He&#8217;ll be using jQuery for examples.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17201"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:13 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Will Anderson getting rolling, talking Ajax and WordPress.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17199"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:13 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>I&#8217;m in the development track, Justin will be in the theme track. Plus, Krogsgard is at it from home. Liveblog to the max. And I&#8217;m uncool again.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17198"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Justin Vela at 10:13 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Sainton not Satin!</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17195"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Justin Vela at 10:12 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17196" title="View from the theme track" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/2011-04-16-10.05.10-600x450.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" /></p><p><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17197" title="View from the theme track" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/2011-04-16-10.05.56-600x450.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="450" /></p><p>I&#8217;ll be in the theme track right now. My current view.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17121"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Justin Vela at 10:11 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Things are getting started in the Theming Track.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17194"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 10:07 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Apparently I&#8217;m really good with time.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17107"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 9:41 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a title="WPCandy thanks The Theme Foundry" href="http://wpcandy.com/thanks/the-theme-foundry">Big thanks to The Theme Foundry</a> for <a title="You can power WPCandy too" href="http://wpcandy.com/is/powered">powering WPCandy</a> to attend WordCamp Seattle this weekend. We literally wouldn&#8217;t be here without them, so check them out and thank them!</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17105"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 9:39 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>If you&#8217;re watching the events today from home, don&#8217;t miss out on the <a title="WordCamp Seattle 2011 live streams" href="http://wpcandy.com/reports/wordcamp-seattle-2011-will-be-live-streamed-today-starting-9am">live streams that the WordCamp Seattle folks are offering up</a>. Just be sure to keep our liveblog up in another tab!</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17192"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 9:01 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Changed timezone of the blog. Always forget stuff like that.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17096"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 8:57 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p><a rel="attachment wp-att-17097" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblog_entry/17096/attachment/img_0018"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17097" title="New mobile office, in Seattle Washington" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0018-e1302961887148-600x800.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="480" /></a></p><p>I&#8217;d like to think I&#8217;ve upgraded a bit since the <a href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblogged/wordcamp-phoenix-2011#liveblog-entry-13645">last time I shared my mobile office</a>. Hopefully it makes my blogging/developing that much better. Because that&#8217;s how it works.</p><p><em>Right?</em></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17095"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 8:46 am -- Saturday</strong></p><p>Up and at &#8216;em. Will be leaving for WordCamp in an hour or so, after which the real liveblogging will get going. T minus 2 hours.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17089"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 6:30 pm -- Friday</strong></p><p><a rel="attachment wp-att-17090" href="http://wpcandy.com/liveblog_entry/17089/attachment/p4cbq"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-17090" title="WordCamp Seattle 2011 venue ready" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/p4cbq-600x448.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="448" /></a></p><p>Sounds like the volunteers and organizers of WordCamp Seattle have wrangled everything together and finished prepping the venue. (<a title="WordCamp Seattle tweet" href="https://twitter.com/wordcampseattle/status/59034918667288577">via</a>)</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17087"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 6:19 pm -- Friday</strong></p><p>I&#8217;ve been asked to mention WP101&#8242;s deal for WordCamp attendees. If you&#8217;re interested in WordPress support videos, and/or getting a good deal, <a title="WP101 for WordCamp attendees" href="http://www.wp101.com/wordcamp">check them out</a>.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17077"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 5:46 pm -- Friday</strong></p><p><strong>Story time. </strong></p><p>The WPCandy crew missed their flight last night by a couple of minutes. So instead we spent the night in Indianapolis, grabbing a flight this morning to Milwaukee, where we have spent the better part of the day on a long layover waiting for our flight to Seattle.</p><p>We missed out on a day hanging out in Seattle, but at least we won&#8217;t miss the main event.</p><p>Did we mention we&#8217;ll need a drink or two tonight in Seattle? Yeah, that&#8217;s going to happen.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17075"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 4:27 pm -- Friday</strong></p><p>One more test.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div><div class="liveblog-entry" id="liveblog-entry-17067"><p class="live-blog-author"><strong>Ryan Imel at 4:16 pm -- Friday</strong></p><p>Just testing out the newly created liveblog. And sitting in Milwaukee being cold.</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17060">The WPCandy WordCamp Seattle 2011 Liveblog</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div></div></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 21:16:58 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:64:"WPCandy: Winners: Results of 16 more Theme Madness Round 1 games";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=17005";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:100:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/oIYWIKx6m-0/theme-madness-2011-round-1-day-2-and-3-winners";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13553:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17005"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17053" title="Theme Madness winners for Round 1 Days 2 and 3" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/thememadnesswinners-round1day23-teaser.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="240" /></a></p><p>The <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness" href="http://wpcandy.com/series-on/theme-madness-2011">Theme Madness</a> tournament has been roaring along really well so far. We’re into our last day of Round 1 voting, with just a few hours left . But today we’re talking about Day 2 and Day 3 winners.</p><p>We have the results of <em>sixteen</em> games, <em>sixteen</em> winners, and a couple of <em>very</em> close calls. We’ll dig in just after the jump.</p><h3>How we scored the games</h3><p>Just to recap, each game was run on three fronts. First, we counted up the polls for each game. Secondly, we counted up votes on Twitter. Finally, we counted up comments generated (if they were) on the competitor’s blogs. Top score won.</p><p><span id="more-17005"></span></p><h3>Results of Graph Paper Press vs. Panda Themes</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>5. Graph Paper Press: 93</span></li><li><span>12. Panda Themes: 42</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Graph Paper Press, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 19</a>.</p><h3>Results of Solostream vs. ThemeShift</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>5. Solostream: 26</span></li><li><span>12. ThemeShift: 91</span></li></ul><p>Winner: ThemeShift, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 19</a>.</p><h3>Results of Theme Hybrid vs. Xtreme Theme</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>5. Theme Hybrid: 76</span></li><li><span>12. Xtreme Theme: 44</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Theme Hybrid, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 19</a>.</p><h3>Results of ThemeJam vs. Startbox</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>5. ThemeJam: 50</span></li><li><span>12. Startbox: 52</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Startbox, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 19</a>.</p><h3>Results of Organic Themes vs. Storefront Themes</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>4. Organic Themes: 79</span></li><li><span>13. Storefront Themes: 22</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Organic Themes, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 19</a>.</p><h3>Results of Theme Garden vs. BlogOhBlog</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>4. Theme Garden: 71</span></li><li><span>13. BlogOhBlog: 29</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Theme Garden, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 19</a>.</p><h3>Results of Crowd Favorite vs. Working Wireframes</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>4. Crowd Favorite: 77</span></li><li><span>13. Working Wireframes: 24</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Crowd Favorite, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 19</a>.</p><h3>Results of Pro Theme Design vs. Themes Kingdom</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>4. Pro Theme Design: 60</span></li><li><span>13. Themes Kingdom: 42</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Pro Theme Design, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 19</a>.</p><h3>Results of Press75 vs. Themes by Bavotasan</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>3. Press75: 90</span></li><li><span>14. Themes by Bavotasan: 28</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Press75, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 20</a>.</p><h3>Results of Headway Themes vs. Aloha Themes</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>3. Headway Themes: 103</span></li><li><span>14. Aloha Themes: 31</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Headway Themes, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 20</a>.</p><h3>Results of Templatic vs. ChimeraThemes</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>3. Templatic: 76</span></li><li><span>14. ChimeraThemes: 21</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Templatic, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 20</a>.</p><h3>Results of Elegant Themes vs. Theme Trust</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>3. Elegant Themes: 227</span></li><li><span>14. Theme Trust: 16</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Elegant Themes, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 20</a>.</p><h3>Results of KreativeThemes vs. Dessign</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>6. KreativeThemes: 82</span></li><li><span>11. Dessign: 30</span></li></ul><p>Winner: KreativeThemes, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 20</a>.</p><h3>Results of WPBundle vs. Catalyst Theme</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>6. WPBundle: 91</span></li><li><span>11. Catalyst Theme: 263</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Catalayst Theme, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 20</a>.</p><h3>Results of Mojo Themes vs. Theme Junkie</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>6. Mojo Themes: 112</span></li><li><span>11. Theme Junkie: 25</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Mojo Themes, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 20</a>.</p><h3>Results of Themify vs. Bizz Themes</h3><p>After totaling up poll votes, Twitter votes, and comments on their respective blogs, the numbers are:</p><ul><li><span>6. Themify: 114</span></li><li><span>11. Bizz Themes: 25</span></li></ul><p>Winner: Themify, who will be competing again <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">on April 20</a>.</p><h3>What do you think of the results so far?</h3><p>We’re beginning to see results show up on the big <a title="Theme Madness 2011 Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">Theme Madness Bracket</a>. How do you think the results are shaking out? Are you surprised by any of the results so far? How are your own personal brackets going?</p><p>Remember, we still have a few hours left to vote for the <a title="Theme Madness Round 1 voting, day 4" href="http://wpcandy.com/announces/theme-madness-2011-round-1-day-4-voting">last few games of Round 1</a>.</p><h3>Updated Theme Madness Schedule</h3><table id="wp-table-reloaded-id-14-no-1" class="wp-table-reloaded wp-table-reloaded-id-14"><thead><tr class="row-1 odd"><th class="column-1"></th><th class="column-2">Bracket A</th><th class="column-3">Bracket B</th><th class="column-4">Bracket C</th><th class="column-5">Bracket D</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="row-2 even"><td class="column-1"><a href="http://wpcandy.com/announces/theme-madness-2011-round-1-day-1-voting">April 11</a></td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://www.woothemes.com/">WooThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://themeopoly.com/">Themeopoly</a></p><p><a href="http://gothemeteam.com/">Theme Team</a> vs. <a href="http://www.appthemes.com/">AppThemes</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://themeforest.net/">ThemeForest</a> vs. <a href="http://biothemes.com/">BioThemes</a></p><p><a href="http://www.gabfire.com/">Gabfire Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://richwp.com/">RichWP</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://www.studiopress.com/">StudioPress</a> vs. <a href="http://www.themebaker.com/">Themebaker</a></p><p><a href="http://flexithemes.com/">FlexiThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://premiumpress.com/">PremiumPress</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://oboxthemes.com/">Obox Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://signaturetheme.com/">Signature Theme</a></p><p><a href="http://www.bandthemer.com/">BandThemer</a> vs. <a href="http://upthemes.com/">UpThemes</a></td></tr><tr class="row-3 odd"><td class="column-1">April 12</td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://graphpaperpress.com/">Graph Paper Press</a> vs. <a href="http://pandathemes.com/">Panda Themes</a></p><p><a href="http://www.organicthemes.com/">Organic Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://storefrontthemes.com/">Storefront Themes</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://www.solostream.com/">Solostream</a> vs. <a href="http://themeshift.com/">ThemeShift</a></p><p><a href="http://themegarden.com/">ThemeGarden</a> vs. <a href="http://www.blogohblog.com/">BlogOhBlog</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://themehybrid.com/">ThemeHybrid</a> vs. <a href="http://xtreme-theme.com/">Xtreme Theme</a></p><p><a href="http://crowdfavorite.com/">Crowd Favorite</a> vs. <a href="http://workingwireframes.com/">Working Wireframes</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://themejam.com/">ThemeJam</a> vs. <a href="http://wpstartbox.com/">Startbox</a></p><p><a href="http://prothemedesign.com/">Pro Theme Design</a> vs. <a href="http://themeskingdom.com/">Themes Kingdom</a></td></tr><tr class="row-4 even"><td class="column-1">April 13</td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://themify.me/">Themify</a> vs. <a href="http://bizzthemes.com/">Bizz Themes</a></p><p><a href="http://www.elegantthemes.com/">Elegant Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://themetrust.com/">Theme Trust</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://www.mojo-themes.com/">Mojo Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.theme-junkie.com/">Theme Junkie</a></p><p><a href="http://templatic.com/">Templatic</a> vs. <a href="http://www.chimerathemes.com/">ChimeraThemes</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://www.wpbundle.com/">WPBundle</a> vs. <a href="http://catalysttheme.com/">Catalyst Theme</a></p><p><a href="http://headwaythemes.com/">Headway Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://alohathemes.com/">Aloha Themes</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://www.kreativethemes.com/">KreativeThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.dessign.net/">Dessign</a></p><p><a href="http://press75.com/">Press75</a> vs. <a href="http://themes.bavotasan.com/">Themes by Bavotasan</a></td></tr><tr class="row-5 odd"><td class="column-1">April 14</td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://www.dev4press.com/">Dev4Press</a> vs. <a href="http://www.indonez.com/">Indonez</a></p><p><a href="http://ithemes.com/">iThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.themewarrior.com/">ThemeWarrior</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://www.wpzoom.com/">WPZoom</a> vs. <a href="http://www.vivathemes.com/">Viva Themes</a></p><p><a href="http://www.pagelines.com/">Pagelines</a> vs.<a href="http://wonderthemes.com/"> Wonder Themes</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://gorillathemes.com/">Gorilla Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://wpshower.com/">WPShower</a></p><p><a href="http://diythemes.com/">DIYThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.theme-force.com/">ThemeForce</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://tokokoo.com/">Tokokoo</a> vs. <a href="http://standardtheme.com/">Standard Theme</a></p><p><a href="http://thethemefoundry.com/">Theme Foundry</a> vs. <a href="http://themefuse.com/">ThemeFuse</a></td></tr><tr class="row-6 even"><td class="column-1">April 18</td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://www.woothemes.com/">WooThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.appthemes.com/">AppThemes</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://themeforest.net/">ThemeForest</a> vs. <a href="http://www.gabfire.com/">Gabfire Themes</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://www.studiopress.com/">StudioPress</a> vs. <a href="http://premiumpress.com/">PremiumPress</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://oboxthemes.com/">Obox Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://upthemes.com/">UpThemes</a></td></tr></tbody></table><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17005">Winners: Results of 16 more Theme Madness Round 1 games</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 20:00:52 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:77:"WPCandy: WordCamp Seattle tickets likely to sell out today with 350 attendees";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=17040";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:92:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/oF0wqIKVMlw/350-attendees-at-wordcamp-seattle-2011";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1543:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17040"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17042" title="WordCamp Seattle tickets selling out (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/wordcampseattletickets-teaser.jpg" alt="" width="578" height="256" /></a></p><p>It appears that <a title="WordCamp Seattle" href="http://wordcampseattle.org/">WordCamp Seattle</a>, the event we&#8217;re <a title="WPCandy will be at WordCamp Seattle 2011" href="http://wpcandy.com/announces/wpcandy-will-be-attending-wordcamp-seattle-2011">attending</a> and <a title="WPCandy coverage of WordCamp Seattle 2011" href="http://wpcandy.com/at/wordcamp-seattle">covering</a> this weekend, will be selling out today. This will bring the attendee number to 350, which is a considerable number for a WordCamp. Tickets were made available in mid March this year, and only a handful remain.</p><p>The remaining tickets are <a title="Register for WordCamp Seattle" href="http://wordcampseattle.org/registration/">available</a> for either $30 for general submission, or $25 for students, but you better act fast. I&#8217;m happy to say WPCandy snatched up four of those tickets, and will be enjoying the festivities this weekend (and of course liveblogging).</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17040">WordCamp Seattle tickets likely to sell out today with 350 attendees</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 18:48:08 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:90:"WPCandy: Preview the upcoming Event Espresso mobile ticketing app (for iPhone and Android)";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=17021";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:105:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/Qet1HrngTlU/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5758:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17021"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17035" title="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/eventespressoapps-teaser.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="250" /></a></p><p>The team at Event Espresso, the popular WordPress event registration plugin (and <a title="Event Espresso powers WPCandy" href="http://wpcandy.com/thanks/event-espresso">friend of WPCandy</a>), have been working hard on iPhone and Android versions of a new mobile app. The app will be for mobile ticketing at events, and reviewing attendee lists. To get a good feel for the app&#8217;s intended functionality, check out the screenshots we have in the gallery below.</p><p>The apps will work in conjunction with the Espresso&#8217;s ticket QR codes, via the add-on they released <a title="Event Espresso QR code ticketing add-on" href="http://eventespresso.com/2011/01/customizable-printable-event-tickets-qr-code/">earlier this year</a>, by scanning the codes at the door to check in attendees.</p><p>Development on the apps <a title="Event Espresso app development begins" href="http://eventespresso.com/2011/02/iphone-android-onsite-check-in-app-development/">began</a> a couple of months ago. The completed apps should be showing up in their respective app stores in the next couple of weeks. What do you think of the screenshots? And how many WordPress plugins would you like to see mobile apps developed for?</p><p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/img_0115" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 01"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0115-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 01" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 01" /></a><br /> <a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/img_0116" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 02"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0116-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 02" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 02" /></a><br /> <a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/img_0117" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 03"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0117-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 03" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 03" /></a><br /> <a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/img_0120" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 04"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0120-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 04" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 04" /></a><br /> <a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/img_0121" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 05"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0121-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 05" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 05" /></a><br /> <a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/img_0122" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 06"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0122-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 06" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 06" /></a><br /> <a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/img_0123" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 07"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0123-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 07" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 07" /></a><br /> <a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/img_0125" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 08"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/IMG_0125-150x150.png" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 08" title="Event Espresso mobile app screenshot 08" /></a><br /> <a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/eventespressoapps-teaser" title="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (teaser)"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/eventespressoapps-teaser-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (teaser)" title="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (teaser)" /></a><br /> <a href="http://wpcandy.com/previewed/the-upcoming-event-espresso-iphone-and-android-apps/attachment/eventespressoapps-thumb" title="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (thumb)"><img width="150" height="150" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/eventespressoapps-thumb-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-thumbnail" alt="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (thumb)" title="Event Espresso iPhone and Android apps (thumb)" /></a></p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17021">Preview the upcoming Event Espresso mobile ticketing app (for iPhone and Android)</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 18:02:36 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"Matt: Tim Ferriss On Facebook, Twitter And Building A Huge Web Brand";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:21:"http://ma.tt/?p=37964";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"http://ma.tt/2011/04/tf-on-wp/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1387:"<div class="blockquote"><blockquote><p>I think there’s a difference between having a bestselling book–meaning through marketing, PR and buying that first wave of customers–and writing a bestselling book. The second implies that the product propels itself to the best seller list. That’s not to say that I’m Tolstoy or the best writer, but I used Facebook and Twitter more for feed back as I was creating and refining the book than for the actual marketing itself. My main online tool for priming the pump for the launch of the book was the blog. That was the heartbeat and the nexus for all the different tools that I use.</p></blockquote></div>\n<p>Via <a href="http://blogs.forbes.com/stevenbertoni/2011/04/14/tim-ferriss-on-facebook-twitter-and-building-a-huge-web-brand/">Tim Ferriss On Facebook, Twitter And Building A Huge Web Brand &#8211; Steven Bertoni &#8211; Money Talks &#8211; Forbes</a>. I also liked this quote:</p>\n<div class="blockquote"><blockquote><p>SB: How can a magazine catch up to the Web?</p>\n<p>TF: If I worked for a magazine that’s very behind the times, I wouldn’t reinvent the wheel. I’d use WordPress as a content management system which has very good SEO out of the box. Companies spend so much time trying to develop something proprietary it’s ridiculous–you have thousands of people already working on WordPress.</p></blockquote></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 17:32:37 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Matt";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:10;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:53:"WPCandy: WordCamp Atlanta 2011 date moves to the fall";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=17016";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:98:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/SvUsP_3sxZI/wordcamp-atlanta-2011-date-moves-to-the-fall";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2257:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17016"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17017" title="WordCamp Atlanta 2011 logo (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/wordcampatlantalogo-teaser.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="239" /></a></p><p>WordCamp Atlanta 2011 was <a title="WordCamp Atlanta is officially scheduled for May 6th and 7th" href="http://wpcandy.com/reports/wordcamp-atlanta-2011-may-6-7">initially scheduled</a> for the beginning of May. Due to the organization team wanting to ensure a larger event than 2010, the event has been pushed back to a yet-to-be announced date this fall.</p><p>Not much was said in the <a title="WordCamp Atlanta date announcement" href="http://atlantawordcamp.com/2011/04/update-wordcamp-atlanta-2011-is-moving-to-fall-2011/">announcement</a>, but organizer Tessa Horehled did share some of their plans for the extra time before this year&#8217;s event:</p><blockquote><p>This year’s event is going to be pushed back to Fall so we can ensure this year’s event even bigger and better than last year, by bringing more great leaders from the Atlanta WordCamp community into the fold and securing a brand new venue which we hope to announce in the coming months.</p></blockquote><p>We&#8217;ll keep an eye out and notify you when WordCamp Atlanta 2011&#8242;s date is firmed up. Until then, who&#8217;s looking forward to the next event in Atlanta?</p><p>I attended last year&#8217;s event, which was fantastic, and <a title="Parent/child theme presentation on Slideshare" href="http://www.slideshare.net/ryanimel/speeding-up-site-development-with-parent-and-child-themes">presented on child themes</a>. I&#8217;m looking forward to attending this year, though I will probably be more focused on <a title="WPCandy covers WordCamps" href="http://wpcandy.com/on/wordcamp">covering WordCamp</a> than I will be trying to present on a particular topic. Who has attended in the past that will be going again this year?</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=17016">WordCamp Atlanta 2011 date moves to the fall </a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 16:43:10 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:11;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Theme Releases for 4/15";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=9891";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/558Z0QN3q9I/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:745:"<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-9892" title="diesel" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/diesel.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="87" /></p>\n<p><a href="http://stockable.net/diesel/"><strong>Diesel</strong></a> is a dark theme designed for video game blogs.</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-9893" title="leathernote" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/leathernote.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="113" /></p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/themes/leathernote"><strong>LeatherNote</strong></a> is a sleek leather notepad design for WordPress.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/558Z0QN3q9I" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 15 Apr 2011 13:00:16 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"James Huff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:12;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:69:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress and the Uneditable Theme Templates";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=9886";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/h3F09z24nqg/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1238:"<p>So, you have a plugin requiring that you make a change to one of your <a href="http://wordpress.org/">WordPress</a> theme templates, or you just want move something around in your theme or alter your CSS. You&#8217;ve arrived at Appearance -&gt; Editor as instructed, but there&#8217;s no &#8220;Update File&#8221; button.</p>\n<p>This is unfortunately another one of those common annoyances related to your hosting provider&#8217;s server configuration that can take you off guard and lead to plenty of confusion. Fortunately, it&#8217;s easy to fix (or work around).</p>\n<p>Try <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Changing_File_Permissions">changing the permissions</a> of the theme files that you want to edit to 666. If that doesn&#8217;t work, just use an <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/FTP_Clients">FTP or SFTP client</a> and a <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Glossary#Text_editor">plain text editor</a> to edit them remotely.</p>\n<p>Of course, if neither of those methods are working out for you, please stop by the <a href="http://wordpress.org/support/">WordPress Support Forums</a> for further assistance.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/h3F09z24nqg" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 14 Apr 2011 13:00:30 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"James Huff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:13;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:53:"WPCandy: Vote here: Theme Madness 2011, Round 1 Day 4";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=16999";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:93:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/0yJsIsdLAfc/theme-madness-2011-round-1-day-4-voting";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:14790:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16999"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-17000" title="Theme Madness Round 1 Day 4 voting (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/thememadnessround1day4voting-teaser.png" alt="" width="600" height="240" /></a></p><p>This week we will be running through Round 1 of <a title="Theme Madness 2011" href="http://wpcandy.com/series-on/theme-madness-2011">Theme Madness</a>, with eight games happening each day. In fact, today is the last day of Round 1 voting. Today’s games will be:</p><ul><li><a href="http://www.dev4press.com/">Dev4Press</a> vs. <a href="http://www.indonez.com/">Indonez</a></li><li><a href="http://tokokoo.com/">Tokokoo</a> vs. <a href="http://standardtheme.com/">Standard Theme</a></li><li><a href="http://www.pagelines.com/">Pagelines</a> vs. <a href="http://wonderthemes.com/">Wonder Themes</a></li><li><a href="http://ithemes.com/">iThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://themewarrior.com/">ThemeWarrior</a></li><li><a href="http://gorillathemes.com/">Gorilla Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://wpshower.com/">WPShower</a></li><li><a href="http://thethemefoundry.com/">The Theme Foundry</a> vs. <a href="http://themefuse.com/">ThemeFuse</a></li><li><a href="http://www.wpzoom.com/">WPZoom</a> vs. <a href="http://www.vivathemes.com/">Viva Themes</a></li><li><a href="http://diythemes.com/">DIYThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.theme-force.com/">ThemeForce</a></li></ul><p>All of the polls and instructions can be found just after the jump, so be sure to click through to have your voice heard. Voting will take place for the next 48 hours, and close at midnight on the 15th (Eastern Standard Time).</p><p>If you need a reminder, the rules can be found <a title="How to win your Theme Madness 2011 Trophy" href="http://wpcandy.com/announces/theme-madness-2011-rules">here</a>. Good luck to everyone playing!</p><p><span id="more-16999"></span></p><h3>Dev4Press vs. Indonez</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4915034"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4915034"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4915034/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">Market Research</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="Dev4Press on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/milangd">@MilanGD</a> or <a title="Indonez on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/indoneztheme">@IndonezTheme</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either Dev4Press or Indonez start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>Tokokoo vs. Standard Theme</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4915051"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4915051"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4915051/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">online surveys</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="Tokokoo on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/tokokoo">@Tokokoo</a> or <a title="Standard Theme on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/standardtheme">@StandardTheme</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either Tokokoo or Standard Theme start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>Pagelines vs. Wonder Themes</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4915043"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4915043"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4915043/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">survey software</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="Pagelines on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/pagelines">@Pagelines</a> or <a title="Wonder Themes on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/wonderthemes">@WonderThemes</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either Pagelines or Wonder Themes start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>iThemes vs. ThemeWarrior</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4915039"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4915039"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4915039/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">Market Research</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="iThemes on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/ithemes">@iThemes</a> or <a title="ThemeWarrior on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/themewarrior">@ThemeWarrior</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either iThemes or ThemeWarrior start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>Gorilla Themes vs. WPShower</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4915048"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4915048"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4915048/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">survey software</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="Gorilla Themes on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/gorillathemes">@GorillaThemes</a> or <a title="WPShower on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/wpshower">@WPShower</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either Gorilla Themes or WPShower start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>The Theme Foundry vs. ThemeFuse</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4915052"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4915052"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4915052/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">customer surveys</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="The Theme Foundry on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/thethemefoundry">@TheThemeFoundry</a> or <a title="ThemeFuse on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/themefuse">@ThemeFuse</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either The Theme Foundry or ThemeFuse start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>WPZoom vs. Viva Themes</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4915040"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4915040"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4915040/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">online survey</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="WPZoom on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/wpzoom">@WPZoom</a> or <a title="Viva Themes on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/vivathemes">@VivaThemes</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either WPZoom or Viva Themes start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>DIYThemes vs. ThemeForce</h3><p><a name="pd_a_4915050"></a><div class="PDS_Poll" id="PDI_container4915050"></div><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4915050/">View This Poll</a><br /><br /><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">online survey</a></span><br /> </p><p>Remember, along with this poll you can also vote two other ways:</p><ul><li><strong>The away game:</strong> Tweet your vote using the <a title="#wpmadness hashtag on Twitter" href="http://search.twitter.com/search?q=%23wpmadness">#wpmadness</a> hashtag and mention either <a title="DIYThemes on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/diythemes">@DIYThemes</a> or <a title="Noel Tock on Twitter" href="http://twitter.com/#!/noeltock">@NoelTock</a>.</li><li><strong>The home game:</strong> If either DIYThemes or ThemeForce start up a post on their blog, your comment there will count as a vote as well.</li></ul><h3>Theme Madness 2011 Game Schedule</h3><table id="wp-table-reloaded-id-14-no-1" class="wp-table-reloaded wp-table-reloaded-id-14"><thead><tr class="row-1 odd"><th class="column-1"></th><th class="column-2">Bracket A</th><th class="column-3">Bracket B</th><th class="column-4">Bracket C</th><th class="column-5">Bracket D</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="row-2 even"><td class="column-1"><a href="http://wpcandy.com/announces/theme-madness-2011-round-1-day-1-voting">April 11</a></td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://www.woothemes.com/">WooThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://themeopoly.com/">Themeopoly</a></p><p><a href="http://gothemeteam.com/">Theme Team</a> vs. <a href="http://www.appthemes.com/">AppThemes</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://themeforest.net/">ThemeForest</a> vs. <a href="http://biothemes.com/">BioThemes</a></p><p><a href="http://www.gabfire.com/">Gabfire Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://richwp.com/">RichWP</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://www.studiopress.com/">StudioPress</a> vs. <a href="http://www.themebaker.com/">Themebaker</a></p><p><a href="http://flexithemes.com/">FlexiThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://premiumpress.com/">PremiumPress</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://oboxthemes.com/">Obox Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://signaturetheme.com/">Signature Theme</a></p><p><a href="http://www.bandthemer.com/">BandThemer</a> vs. <a href="http://upthemes.com/">UpThemes</a></td></tr><tr class="row-3 odd"><td class="column-1">April 12</td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://graphpaperpress.com/">Graph Paper Press</a> vs. <a href="http://pandathemes.com/">Panda Themes</a></p><p><a href="http://www.organicthemes.com/">Organic Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://storefrontthemes.com/">Storefront Themes</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://www.solostream.com/">Solostream</a> vs. <a href="http://themeshift.com/">ThemeShift</a></p><p><a href="http://themegarden.com/">ThemeGarden</a> vs. <a href="http://www.blogohblog.com/">BlogOhBlog</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://themehybrid.com/">ThemeHybrid</a> vs. <a href="http://xtreme-theme.com/">Xtreme Theme</a></p><p><a href="http://crowdfavorite.com/">Crowd Favorite</a> vs. <a href="http://workingwireframes.com/">Working Wireframes</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://themejam.com/">ThemeJam</a> vs. <a href="http://wpstartbox.com/">Startbox</a></p><p><a href="http://prothemedesign.com/">Pro Theme Design</a> vs. <a href="http://themeskingdom.com/">Themes Kingdom</a></td></tr><tr class="row-4 even"><td class="column-1">April 13</td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://themify.me/">Themify</a> vs. <a href="http://bizzthemes.com/">Bizz Themes</a></p><p><a href="http://www.elegantthemes.com/">Elegant Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://themetrust.com/">Theme Trust</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://www.mojo-themes.com/">Mojo Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.theme-junkie.com/">Theme Junkie</a></p><p><a href="http://templatic.com/">Templatic</a> vs. <a href="http://www.chimerathemes.com/">ChimeraThemes</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://www.wpbundle.com/">WPBundle</a> vs. <a href="http://catalysttheme.com/">Catalyst Theme</a></p><p><a href="http://headwaythemes.com/">Headway Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://alohathemes.com/">Aloha Themes</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://www.kreativethemes.com/">KreativeThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.dessign.net/">Dessign</a></p><p><a href="http://press75.com/">Press75</a> vs. <a href="http://themes.bavotasan.com/">Themes by Bavotasan</a></td></tr><tr class="row-5 odd"><td class="column-1">April 14</td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://www.dev4press.com/">Dev4Press</a> vs. <a href="http://www.indonez.com/">Indonez</a></p><p><a href="http://ithemes.com/">iThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.themewarrior.com/">ThemeWarrior</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://www.wpzoom.com/">WPZoom</a> vs. <a href="http://www.vivathemes.com/">Viva Themes</a></p><p><a href="http://www.pagelines.com/">Pagelines</a> vs.<a href="http://wonderthemes.com/"> Wonder Themes</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://gorillathemes.com/">Gorilla Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://wpshower.com/">WPShower</a></p><p><a href="http://diythemes.com/">DIYThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.theme-force.com/">ThemeForce</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://tokokoo.com/">Tokokoo</a> vs. <a href="http://standardtheme.com/">Standard Theme</a></p><p><a href="http://thethemefoundry.com/">Theme Foundry</a> vs. <a href="http://themefuse.com/">ThemeFuse</a></td></tr><tr class="row-6 even"><td class="column-1">April 18</td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://www.woothemes.com/">WooThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://www.appthemes.com/">AppThemes</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://themeforest.net/">ThemeForest</a> vs. <a href="http://www.gabfire.com/">Gabfire Themes</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://www.studiopress.com/">StudioPress</a> vs. <a href="http://premiumpress.com/">PremiumPress</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://oboxthemes.com/">Obox Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://upthemes.com/">UpThemes</a></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16999">Vote here: Theme Madness 2011, Round 1 Day 4</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 14 Apr 2011 08:31:33 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:14;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:64:"WPCandy: WPCandy will be attending WordCamp Seattle this weekend";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=16980";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:101:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/5JddyBHRqY4/wpcandy-will-be-attending-wordcamp-seattle-2011";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1896:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16980"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-15873" title="WordCamp Seattle 2011 logo (teaser)" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/03/wordcampseattle-teaser.png" alt="" width="600" height="181" /></a></p><p>I&#8217;m happy to say that WPCandy will be attending <a href="http://wordcampseattle.org/" title="WordCamp Seattle">WordCamp Seattle</a> this coming weekend. The big event is Saturday, and we&#8217;ll be there the whole time handing out WPCandy shirts, liveblogging, and hopefully absorbing some of the excess intelligence in the room.</p><p>Will you be attending this weekend? If so, be sure to let us know so we can say hi and get you a shirt (at least until we run out!). And hey, if you won&#8217;t be there this weekend, head after the jump and let us know what you&#8217;re most interested in seeing from us during the event. We have some ideas, but then again you folks always have great thoughts too!</p><p>Big <a href="http://wpcandy.com/thanks/the-theme-foundry" title="WPCandy thanks The Theme Foundry!">thanks to The Theme Foundry</a> for powering WPCandy to attend WordCamp Seattle this year. And if you haven&#8217;t considered it before, remember that you too can <a href="http://wpcandy.com/is/powered" title="WPCandy is powered by the community">power WPCandy</a>.</p><p><span id="more-16980"></span></p><p><br /> <br /> <a href="http://polldaddy.com/poll/4912071/">What do you want to see WPCandy doing at WordCamp Seattle this weekend?</a><span><a href="http://polldaddy.com/features-surveys/">customer surveys</a></span><br /> </p><div class="tentblogger-rss-footer"><p>You just finished reading <a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16980">WPCandy will be attending WordCamp Seattle this weekend</a> on <a href="http://wpcandy.com" title="WPCandy WordPress community news">WPCandy</a>. Please consider leaving a comment!</p><p></p></div>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 13 Apr 2011 19:25:34 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Ryan Imel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:15;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Plugin Releases for 4/13";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=9883";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/_Nm_MZNDbww/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1521:"<h3>New plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://blog.no-panic.at/projects/foursquare-latest-checkins-wordpress-widget-plugin/"><strong>Foursquare Latest Checkins</strong></a> allows you to show your recent Foursquare checkins and the venue icon as a Widget in your blog’s sidebar.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/static-html-output-plugin/"><strong>WP Static HTML Output</strong></a> produces a static HTML version of your WordPress install, incredibly useful for anyone who would like the publishing power of WordPress but whose webhost doesn&#8217;t allow dynamic PHP driven sites &#8211; such as MobileMe.</p>\n<h3>Updated plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/add-to-any/"><strong>AddToAny: Share/Bookmark/Email Button</strong></a> helps people share, bookmark, and email your posts and pages using any service, such as Facebook, Twitter, Google Buzz, Digg, Delicious, and well over 100 more social bookmarking and sharing sites.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/cart66-lite/"><strong>Cart66 Lite</strong></a> is a simple to use yet powerful eCommerce plugin for WordPress.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/theme-check/"><strong>Theme-Check</strong></a> allows you to run checks on the current theme before uploading to WordPress. This plugin uses the same API and is kept more or less in sync with the WordPress.org uploader tool.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/_Nm_MZNDbww" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 13 Apr 2011 13:00:44 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"James Huff";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:16;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"WPCandy: Winners: First group of Round 1 Theme Madness winners";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://wpcandy.com/?p=16942";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:97:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpcandy/~3/2AUZ5ENt81U/winners-first-group-of-round-1-game-winners";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11820:"<p><a href="http://wpcandy.com/?p=16942"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16943" title="Theme Madness Round 1 Day 1 Winners" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/thememadnessround1day1winners-teaser.png" alt="" width="600" height="240" /></a></p><p>The <a title="WPCandy Theme Madness" href="http://wpcandy.com/series-on/theme-madness-2011">Theme Madness</a> tournament has been roaring along really well so far. We&#8217;re into our <a title="Third day of Theme Madness voting" href="http://wpcandy.com/announces/theme-madness-2011-round-1-day-3-voting">third day of voting</a>, with just a few hours left in the second day. But today we&#8217;re talking about Day 1 winners.</p><p>We have the results of eight games, eight winners, and one <em>very</em> close call. We&#8217;ll dig in just after the jump.</p><p><span id="more-16942"></span></p><h3>How we scored the games</h3><p>Just to recap, each game was run on three fronts. First, we counted up the polls for each game. Secondly, we counted up votes on Twitter. Finally, we counted up comments generated (if they were) on the competitor&#8217;s blogs. Top score won.</p><h3>Results of WooThemes vs. Themeopoly</h3><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16947" title="WooThemes vs. Themeopoly" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/woothemesvsthemeopoly.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><ul><li><span>1. WooThemes: 336 points</span></li><li><span>16. Themeopoly: 46 points</span></li></ul><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16946" title="The Winner is WooThemes" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/winner-woothemes.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><p>WooThemes now goes on to Round 2, where they will be in another match next week on April 18.</p><h3>Results of Theme Team vs. AppThemes</h3><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16949" title="AppThemes vs. Theme Team" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/appthemesvsthemeteam.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><ul><li><span>9. AppThemes: 110</span></li><li><span>8. Theme Team: 51</span></li></ul><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16950" title="The Winner is AppThemes" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/winner-appthemes.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><p>AppThemes now moves on to Round 2, where they will be in another match next week on April 18, against WooThemes.</p><h3>Results of ThemeForest vs. BioThemes</h3><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16952" title="BioThemes vs. ThemeForest" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/biothemesvsthemeforest.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><ul><li><span>1. ThemeForest: 324</span></li><li><span>16. BioThemes: 48</span></li></ul><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16953" title="ThemeForest is the winner" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/winner-themeforest.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><p>ThemeForest now moves on to Round 2, where they will be in another match next week on April 18.</p><h3>Results of Gabfire Themes vs. RichWP</h3><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16954" title="Gabfire Theme vs RichWP" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/gabfirevsrichwp.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><ul><li><span>8. Gabfire Themes: 82</span></li><li><span>9. RichWP: 79</span></li></ul><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16955" title="The Winner is Gabfire Themes" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/winner-gabfire.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><p>Gabfire Themes now moves on to Round 2, where they will be in another match next week on April 18, up against ThemeForest.</p><h3>Results of StudioPress vs. Themebaker</h3><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16965" title="StudioPress vs. Themebaker" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/studiopressvsthemebaker.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><ul><li><span>1. StudioPress: 156</span></li><li><span>16. Themebaker: 37</span></li></ul><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16966" title="StudioPress is the Winner" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/winner-studiopress.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><p>StudioPress now moves on to Round 2, where they will be in another match next week on April 18.</p><h3>Results of FlexiThemes vs. PremiumPress</h3><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16957" title="FlexiThemes vs. PremiumPress" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/flexithemesvspremiumpress.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><ul><li><span>8. FlexiThemes: 51</span></li><li><span>9. PremiumPress: 85</span></li></ul><p><img title="PremiumPress is the Winner" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/winner-premiumpress.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><p>PremiumPress now moves on to Round 2, where they will be in another match next week on April 18 against StudioPress.</p><h3>Results of Obox Themes vs. Signature Theme</h3><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16961" title="Signature vs. Obox" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/signaturevsobox.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><ul><li><span>1. Obox Themes: 135</span></li><li><span>16. Signature Theme: 37</span></li></ul><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16962" title="Obox is the Winner" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/winner-obox.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><p>Obox Themes now moves on to Round 2, where they will be in another match next week on April 18.</p><h3>Results of BandThemer vs. UpThemes</h3><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16967" title="UpThemes vs. BandThemer" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/upthemesvsbandthemer.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><ul><li><span>8. BandThemer: 33</span></li><li><span>9. UpThemes: 97</span></li></ul><p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-16968" title="UpThemes is the Winner" src="http://wpcandy.com/files/2011/04/winner-upthemes.png" alt="" width="600" height="90" /></p><p>UpThemes now moves on to Round 2, where they will be in another match next week on April 18, against Obox Themes.</p><h3>What do you think of the results so far?</h3><p>We&#8217;re beginning to see results show up on the big <a title="Theme Madness Bracket" href="http://wpcandy.com/theme-madness">Theme Madness Bracket</a>. How do you think the results are shaking out? Are you surprised by any of the results so far? How are your own personal brackets going?</p><h3>Updated Theme Madness Schedule</h3><table id="wp-table-reloaded-id-14-no-1" class="wp-table-reloaded wp-table-reloaded-id-14"><thead><tr class="row-1 odd"><th class="column-1"></th><th class="column-2">Bracket A</th><th class="column-3">Bracket B</th><th class="column-4">Bracket C</th><th class="column-5">Bracket D</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="row-2 even"><td class="column-1"><a href="http://wpcandy.com/announces/theme-madness-2011-round-1-day-1-voting">April 11</a></td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://www.woothemes.com/">WooThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://themeopoly.com/">Themeopoly</a></p><p><a href="http://gothemeteam.com/">Theme Team</a> vs. <a href="http://www.appthemes.com/">AppThemes</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://themeforest.net/">ThemeForest</a> vs. <a href="http://biothemes.com/">BioThemes</a></p><p><a href="http://www.gabfire.com/">Gabfire Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://richwp.com/">RichWP</a></td><td class="column-4"><a href="http://www.studiopress.com/">StudioPress</a> vs. <a href="http://www.themebaker.com/">Themebaker</a></p><p><a href="http://flexithemes.com/">FlexiThemes</a> vs. <a href="http://premiumpress.com/">PremiumPress</a></td><td class="column-5"><a href="http://oboxthemes.com/">Obox Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://signaturetheme.com/">Signature Theme</a></p><p><a href="http://www.bandthemer.com/">BandThemer</a> vs. <a href="http://upthemes.com/">UpThemes</a></td></tr><tr class="row-3 odd"><td class="column-1">April 12</td><td class="column-2"><a href="http://graphpaperpress.com/">Graph Paper Press</a> vs. <a href="http://pandathemes.com/">Panda Themes</a></p><p><a href="http://www.organicthemes.com/">Organic Themes</a> vs. <a href="http://storefrontthemes.com/">Storefront Themes</a></td><td class="column-3"><a href="http://www.solostream.com/">Solostream</a> vs. <a href="http://themeshift.com/">ThemeShift</a></p><p><a href="http://themegarden.com/">ThemeGarden</a> vs. <a href="http://www.blogohblog.com/">BlogOhBlog</a></td><td class="column-4"><